Explanation:
The solution iterates through the string half of the string at a time, comparing the characters at corresponding positions. If any pair of characters doesn't match, the function returns false immediately. Since the string is checked in pairs, the time complexity is O(n), where n is the string length. The space complexity is O(1) because only a constant amount of space is used for the input string and the function doesn't require any additional data structures.

